	]}
	faithsHeading="What “our Father” offers India"
	faithsIntroHtml={`India is home to Hindus, Muslims, Buddhists, Sikhs, Jains, and millions seeking. The Father&rsquo;s Heart Bible&trade; does not erase that search &mdash; it answers the longing underneath it. For the first time in English, Scripture reveals God not as a remote deity to appease, but as a <em>Father</em> who runs to meet His children.`}
	faithsBlocks={[
		{ heading: 'For the one seeking intimacy', bodyHtml: `Many faiths reach toward the divine through ritual and distance. The Father&rsquo;s Heart Bible&trade; reveals a God who reaches first &mdash; <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/john/3" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">&ldquo;our Father so loved the world&rdquo;</a> &mdash; offering not a transaction but a relationship, closeness instead of fear.` },
		{ heading: 'For the one longing to belong', bodyHtml: `In a land of caste, class, and a billion striving souls, the Father calls every person &mdash; rich or poor, high or low &mdash; His beloved son or daughter. Belonging is no longer earned; it is given.` },
		{ heading: 'For the one carrying shame or debt', bodyHtml: `To the farmer crushed by debt and the family broken by addiction, the Father offers a home with no ledger of wrongs &mdash; the relief of being received, not judged.` },
		{ heading: 'For the one without hope', bodyHtml: `Where despair drives so many to the edge, the Father speaks <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/jeremiah/29" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">a future and a hope</a> &mdash; identity, intimacy, and inheritance that no circumstance can take away.` },
	]}
	whyHeading="Why the Father's Heart Bible™ for India"
